org.dockbox.selene.api.files

Class FileManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.dockbox.selene.api.files.FileManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    InjectableType
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefaultAbstractFileManager

    public abstract class FileManager
extends java.lang.Object
implements InjectableType
    Low-level interface defining functionality to interact with Configurate based file types. While this type encourages the usage of Configurate based instances, it is possible to create implementations for alternative configuration libraries and/or frameworks.

      • read

        public abstract <T> Exceptional<T> read(java.nio.file.Path file,
                                        java.lang.Class<T> type)
        Get the content of a file, and map the given values to a generic type T. The exact file is completely dynamic, though it is usually encouraged to use getDataFile(java.lang.Class<?>) or getConfigFile(java.lang.Class<?>) to obtain appropriate files.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type parameter of the type to map to
        Parameters:
        file - The file to read the content of
        type - The exact type to map to
        Returns:
        A Exceptional instance holding either the mapping T instance, or a Throwable

      • write

        public abstract <T> Exceptional<java.lang.Boolean> write(java.nio.file.Path file,
                                                         T content)
        Write a generic type T to a given file. The exact file is completely dynamic, though it is usually encouraged to use getDataFile(java.lang.Class<?>) or getConfigFile(java.lang.Class<?>) to obtain appropriate files.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type parameter of the content
        Parameters:
        file - The file to write the content of
        content - The content to write
        Returns:
        A Exceptional instance holding a Boolean indicating the success status of the write process, or a Throwable. If a Throwable is present, the Boolean value should be false.
